#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:1
msgid "What to do in difficult situations?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:3
msgid ""
"It may be that not everything goes exactly as planned (ex. stormy "
"weather, grumpy volunteers, unhappy neighbours, flat tire, etc.). If you "
"find yourself in a difficult situation, and you don't know what to do, "
"our recommendations are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:5
msgid "Consult the Pick-Leader Guides. If you are still not sure ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:6
msgid "Look at the Annexes! If you are still not sure..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:7
msgid "Use your problem-solving skills."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:9
msgid ""
"If you encounter a non-urgent issue that requires follow-up, please "
"contact us at "
"[info@lesfruitsdefendus.org](mailto:info@lesfruitsdefendus.org) or leave "
"a voice message at our phone number: 514-360-8566. Please understand that"
" we will not be able to respond immediately. You may also try contacting "
"your fruit buddy or another pick-leader for advice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:11
msgid ""
"In case of emergency involving personal safety during a pick, call 911 "
"immediately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:13
msgid "In case you must cancel or re-schedule a harvest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:15
msgid ""
"If you need to cancel a harvest for any reason, you must advise the "
"volunteer pickers, the owner of the tree and the beneficiary organization"
" as soon as possible. You may consider re- scheduling the harvest rather "
"than cancelling, if this is an option for you, keeping in mind that in "
"this case, you will still need to follow up with the volunteer pickers, "
"the owner of the tree and the beneficiary organization as soon as "
"possible. Contact your fruit buddy if you need support re-scheduling a "
"pick."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:17
msgid "In case of lightning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:19
msgid ""
"We do often pick fruit in the rain (although the rain can make the tree's"
" branches and ladders slippery), but we do not pick in thunderstorms. "
"It's important to remember that both trees and metal ladders can attract "
"lightning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:21
msgid ""
"For this reason, it's very important that you remain aware of the weather"
" forecast for your harvest date. That being said, since the weather "
"forecasts in the Montreal area are often quite unpredictable, it can be "
"difficult to judge in advance whether or not to proceed with a pick."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:23
msgid ""
"For this reason, unless the forecast calls for a very high probability of"
" thunderstorms during your scheduled harvest time, it may be better just "
"to proceed with the harvest. In this situation, we recommend advising the"
" tree owner and volunteer pickers that you may have to cancel (or re-"
"schedule) the harvest upon very short notice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:25
msgid ""
"If, upon arrival at the site, you find that the pick cannot be conducted "
"safely, you can choose to cancel the harvest immediately. However, we ask"
" that you remain on site – under shelter of a building, if possible – "
"until all of the volunteers have arrived or at least 15 minutes after the"
" agreed upon time of harvest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:27
msgid "In case of disruption or damage to the tree or property"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:29
msgid ""
"Of course, we hope that this never happens, but should the tree or "
"property be disrupted or damaged in some way, it is important that you "
"let the tree owner and your fruit buddy know as soon as possible. We "
"understand that unexpected accidents can occur, but please remember that "
"tree owners put their trust in us, and therefore it's important for us to"
" communicate openly and help them understand the situation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/source/harvest-guide/difficult-situations.md:31
msgid ""
"After having communicated the situation to the tree owner, you may direct"
" him or her to contact the collective's core (by email: "
"[info@lesfruitsdefendus.org](mailto:info@lesfruitsdefendus.org)), if any "
"further discussion needs to take place. The core will follow up, if "
"necessary."
msgstr ""

